#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/production-orders.adoc:4
msgid ""
"Factory gauges set to the xref:factory-gauge.adoc#production-orders[\"follow "
"demand and order\" mode] allow their products to be manually ordered from a "
"stock keeper tuned to the same network. In stock keeper UI, each gauge in "
"this mode appears as a production task, signified by a blueprint background."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/production-orders.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Click to add the production task to the order, and adjust the amount per "
"usual. Sending an order containing production tasks creates a production "
"order, causing the corresponding factory gauges to add the number of items "
"in the order to their demands. When the produced items arrive in the "
"logistic network, they are sent out again to the address specified on the "
"order."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/production-orders.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Pending production orders can be viewed in the \"production orders\" tab in "
"the stock keeper UI. They are automatically removed when all ordered items "
"arrive in the logistic network, or stuck if they never arrive."
msgstr ""

